# CMS (placeholder)

Future CMS app for managing blog content. Currently a placeholder — all blog logic (article data, FAQ, meta) lives as local mocks in `apps/web/src/constans/`.

## Planned approach

A Markdown-based CMS using shared components from `@my-monorepo/components`.

## Planned flow

1. Create an article draft (Markdown) → save to PostgreSQL (via backend API)
2. Publish article → change flag in the database from `draft` to `published`
3. Backend caches published articles in Redis for faster HTTP responses
4. Frontend (`apps/web`) fetches articles from the API and renders them via `react-markdown`

## Dependencies on existing elements

| Element                                      | Package/App                    | Status                                   |
| -------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------- |
| UI components (Button, Form, TextArea, etc.) | `@my-monorepo/components`      | ready                                    |
| Design tokens + themes                       | `@my-monorepo/styles`          | ready                                    |
| Markdown rendering                           | `react-markdown` in `apps/web` | ready                                    |
| Blog layout + routing                        | `apps/web/src/features/blog/`  | ready (with mocks)                       |
| API (NestJS)                                 | `apps/backend`                 | base setup ready                         |
| Database (Prisma)                            | `apps/backend`                 | adapter-pg ready, schema needs expansion |
| Cache (Redis)                                | `apps/backend`                 | get/set service ready                    |

## Security

When implementing the CMS, remember to sanitize HTML on the client side — `DOMPurify` prevents XSS attacks.

Dependency to add: [DOMPurify](https://github.com/cure53/DOMPurify)
